Allows you to send email using Amazon Ses

application.conf should contain a line: include "mail.conf"

mail.conf should contain the following information:

mail.smtp.host="smtp.host.com"
mail.smtp.port=25
mail.smtp.username=""
mail.smtp.password=""


Usage is as follows:

Ses.sendEmail(Email(
        subject = "Test mail",
        from = EmailAddress("Erik Westra sender", "ewestra@rhinofly.nl"),
        recipients = List(Recipient(Message.RecipientType.TO, EmailAddress("Erik Westra recipient", "ewestra@rhinofly.nl"))),
        text = "text",
        htmlText = "htmlText",
        attachments = Seq.empty))

